5.  Write a for loop to calculate the sum of all integers from 1 to 100.
6.  Write a for loop that prints only the even numbers from 1 to 20.
7.  Write a for loop to print the first 10 multiples of 5 (e.g., 5, 10, 15, ...).
8.  Given a positive integer (e.g., 12345), write a for loop to reverse its digits and print the reversed number.
9.  Write a for loop to print all prime numbers between 1 and 50. (A prime number is a number greater than 1 that has no divisors other than 1 and itself.)
10. Write a for loop to reverse a given string
